HOUSE BILL 1402
By Hicks G
SENATE BILL 1394
By Watson
AN ACT pursuant to Article II, Section 24, of the
Tennessee Constitution providing for the dollar
amount and rate by which the growth of
appropriations from state tax revenues will exceed
the estimated growth in the state's economy and
to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 9,
Chapter 4, Part 52.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 9-4-5203(a), is amended by deleting
the language "for the fiscal year in progress, for the latest completed calendar year, and for
calendar year 1977." and substituting instead the language "for the fiscal year in progress and
for the latest completed calendar year.".
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 9-4-5203(b), is amended by deleting
the language "for the ensuing fiscal year, such actual appropriations for the fiscal year in
progress, and the 1977-1978 fiscal year appropriations from state tax revenues." and
substituting instead the language "for the ensuing fiscal year and such actual appropriations for
the fiscal year in progress.".
SECTION 3. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
